Market Segmentation: 
Mining automation market is segmented on the basis of technique, workflow and type. The growth among segments helps you analyse niche pockets of growth and strategies to approach the market and determine your core application areas and the difference in your target markets.
Mining automation market on the basis of technique has been segmented as surface mining technique, and underground mining technique.
Based on workflow, the mining automation market has been segmented into mine development, mining process, and mine maintenance. Mine development has been further segmented into tunnel boring, construction of access roads, and site preparation and clearing. Mining process has been further segmented into autonomous haulage, and automated drilling. Mine maintenance has been further segmented into Hvac, and mine dewatering.
On the basis of type, the mining automation market has been segmented into equipment, software, and communications system. Equipment has been further segmented into autonomous hauling/mining truck, autonomous drilling rig, underground LHD loader, tunnelling equipment, smart ventilations system, pumping stations, and others. Others have been further sub segmented into hybrid shovels, and total stations. Software has been further segmented into workforce management, proximity detection and collision avoidance system, air quality and temperature monitoring system, fleet management, remote operating and monitoring, data management, and others. Others have been further sub segmented into asset tracking solution, and payload monitoring. Communications system has been further segmented into wireless mesh networks, navigation system, and radio-frequency identification (RFID) tag. 
